This category is about help with '''''Emacs'''''. See also CategoryDocumentation.

== Newbie and not-so-newbie ==
* '''EmacsNewbie''' '''''<===== START HERE'''''
* CategoryGlossary -- Emacs jargon explained
* EmacsNewbieHelpReference
* EmacsNewbieKeyReference


==Emacs help from within Emacs ==

* AproposMode -- Search Emacs for commands, documentation, variables, and more
* ElectricHelp
* InfoMode -- ''complete'' Emacs documentation: `C-h i', then click ''Emacs''
* LearnEmacsLisp -- Using EmacsLisp with Emacs is helpful.
* SelfDocumentation -- quick reference on finding help within Emacs

==Emacs help from the Internet==

* '''OnlineResources''' -- help on the Internet, mailing lists, newsgroups, tutorials...
* EmacsScreencasts
* EmacsChannel -- InternetRelayChat, IRC
* OpenQuestions -- questions and answers about Emacs posted on the wiki
* CategoryReferenceSheet -- Cheat Sheets and command/keybinding xrefs
* [http://emacs.stackexchange.com/ Stack Exchange site dedicated to Emacs]

==Personal initialization files==

* CategoryDotEmacs
* EmacsMacro

==Loading Emacs libraries==

* InstallingPackages -- how to load EmacsLisp libraries.

==Packages that extend or modify standard Emacs help==

* AproposUnicode -- apropos for Unicode characters
* EmacsReflector (speak-freely conference server)
* HelpPlus -- new help commands, improved standard help commands, new key bindings
* HelpMenuBarPlus -- improved '''Help''' menu (menubar)
* HelpModePlus -- click a library name in buffer <code>*Help*</code> to visit the library itself
* [[Icicles]] -- get ''apropos''-style help on everything, as you use it or come across it. See [[Icicles - Help on Candidates]].
* InfoHelp -- Makes symbol names in Info buffer to help links
* InfoLook -- lookup info documentation for functions, variables etc. in many major modes
* ReferenceSheetHelpUtils -- Help Emacs help you help Emacs help you...
* UsageMemo -- integration of Emacs help system and memo
* [http://user42.tuxfamily.org/help-xref-elfiles/index.html help-xref-elfiles.el] -- buttonize <code>foo.el</code> and <code>.emacs</code> in docstrings

